        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1131246465" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16422612037968972739"><u>The Good</u>:<br/>So amazing! Great characters, great setting, great ideas, epic scope, and so well written. This is a science fiction story presented like mythology and it works. Did I mention it&apos;s funny too?<br/><br/><u>The Bad</u>:<br/>The only thing really wrong with this is that the story races ahead of the reader, daring you to try and keep up. It&apos;s not often that I think a book should be longer, but in the case of this one it needed more exposition.<br/><br/><u>&apos;Friends&apos; character the protagonist is most like</u>:<br/>Sam is cynical, driven</span>
  <span id="freeText16422612037968972739" style="display:none"><u>The Good</u>:<br />So amazing! Great characters, great setting, great ideas, epic scope, and so well written. This is a science fiction story presented like mythology and it works. Did I mention it's funny too?<br /><br /><u>The Bad</u>:<br />The only thing really wrong with this is that the story races ahead of the reader, daring you to try and keep up. It's not often that I think a book should be longer, but in the case of this one it needed more exposition.<br /><br /><u>'Friends' character the protagonist is most like</u>:<br />Sam is cynical, driven, and the sanest god in the room. He mostly exists to show how freaky everyone else is, much like Monica.</span>
  <a data-text-id="16422612037968972739" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

